This paper deals with the synthesis of images using GANs, which is a popular topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of few training examples, which is a common challenge in medical image analysis, suggesting a possible fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of GANs also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions boosting image analysis performance, which could fall under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with medical images, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
